I divided the giant macro FitAllHistos.C in three smallest macro. In that way, I think it's easier to run analyzation of 
result because there is no useless info if I run one of these macro (for example if i have to write only the .txt file to 
collect p1 and err_p1 values I don't need multigraph lines too). There is only one constrain: we must to run macro in 
following steps:
1. FitPeaks.C because this macro creates plots of gaussian fits on Charge histo 
2. ExtractGains.C because this macro creates file.txt to collect p1 and p1 error and saves p1 plot 
3. PlotMultiGraph.C because it opens .root file created in step one and checks good or bad p1 values from p1 plot saved by 
   second step.
